 <text id="F0905T"> 
 <front id="d2"> 
 <div1 type="summary" id="d3"> 
 <p>McElheney discusses plans for raising sheep on the family farm.  He also  
 tells his wife  
 that he sent her money and reassures her that he is doing well.</p>  
 </div1>  
 </front>  
 <body id="d4"> 
 <div1 type="letter" id="d5"> 
 <opener> 
 <name type="recipient">Harriet McElheney</name>  
 <dateline> 
 <date value="1865-03-20">March the 20th, 1865</date>  
     <name type="place">Camp in Front of Petersburg</name>  
 </dateline>  
 <salute>Dear Wife,</salute>  
 </opener>  
  
 <p>It is with the <orig reg="greatest">grtest</orig> of <orig  
 reg="pleasure">pleser</orig> that I take the present <orig  
 reg="opportunity">oppertunity</orig> to <orig reg="answer">anser</orig> your  
 kind letter which <orig reg="came to hand">comtohand</orig> on <orig  
 reg="Friday">fryday</orig> night and was glad to hear <orig  
 reg="once">wonst</orig> more from you for I <orig reg="began">begin</orig> to  
 think that you <orig reg="were">was</orig> going to quit <orig  
 reg="writing">riting</orig> to me but I think you <orig  
 reg="haven't">havent</orig> <orig reg="forgotten">forgot</orig> altogether.  I  
 am <orig reg="well">wel</orig> and <orig reg="getting">getin</orig> <orig  
 reg="along">A long</orig> <orig reg="very">verry</orig> <orig  
 reg="well">wel</orig> and I hope <orig reg="when">whan</orig> <orig  
 reg="these">thes</orig> <orig reg="few lines">feulines</orig> <orig  
 reg="reach">reaches</orig> you <orig reg="they">tha</orig> <orig  
 reg="may">ma</orig> find <orig reg="all">awl</orig> <orig  
 reg="well">wel</orig>.</p>  
  
 <p><orig reg="Well">Wel</orig> I must <orig reg="tell">tel</orig> you that we  
 <orig reg="have">hev</orig> <orig reg="been">bean</orig> making <orig  
 reg="breastworks">brestworks</orig> for <orig reg="several">severl</orig> days  
 and <orig reg="there">thair</orig> is A lot<pb n="2"/> of the boys out <orig  
 reg="today">to Day</orig> and I think I <orig reg="will">wil</orig> <orig  
 reg="have to">heftto</orig> go <orig reg="tomorrow">tomrrow</orig> but I <orig  
 reg="would">wod</orig> <orig reg="about">A bout</orig> as soon <orig reg="go  
 out">gout</orig> as stay in camp for we <orig reg="don't">Dont</orig> <orig  
 reg="do very">doverry</orig> much when we <orig reg="are">ar</orig> out.  <orig  
 reg="Well">Wel</orig> you <orig reg="were">wer</orig> talking about them <orig  
 reg="sheep">sheap</orig>.  I think you better <orig reg="give">giv</orig> them  
 to him but if <orig reg="they">tha</orig> <orig reg="have">hev</orig> <orig  
 reg="any">eney</orig> <orig reg="lambs">lames</orig> this spring I <orig  
 reg="don't">dont</orig> <orig reg="want">wot</orig> you to <orig  
 reg="give">giv</orig> him <orig reg="any">eney</orig> of them for I <orig  
 reg="would">wod</orig> sooner pay <orig reg="pasture">paster</orig> for them.  I  
 am going to <orig reg="write">rite</orig> to <unclear>Stribker</unclear> to see  
 how them <orig reg="sheep">sheap</orig> is doing I <orig reg="have">hev</orig> A  
 mind to <orig reg="leave">lev</orig> him <orig reg="have">hev</orig> them <orig  
 reg="another">A nother</orig> year <orig reg="well">wel</orig></p>   
  
 <p>Hally I think if <unclear>McAnasky</unclear> will take them <orig  
 reg="sheep">sheap</orig> I <orig reg="will">wil</orig><pb n="3"/> <orig  
 reg="give">giv</orig> them to him so you <orig reg="can">kin</orig> see him and  
 let me know and if he <orig reg="don't">dont</orig> <orig reg="want">wont</orig>  
 him I <orig reg="will">wil</orig> let <unclear>Stribker</unclear> keep them  
 <orig reg="another">A nother</orig> year I <orig reg="want">wont</orig> you to  
 see him and let me <orig reg="know">now</orig> as soon as you <orig  
 reg="can">kin</orig>.  I suppose Pap will take his home this <orig  
 reg="summer">somer</orig> and he <orig reg="can">kin</orig> take yours over  
 <orig reg="along">A long</orig>.   I <orig reg="expressed">expres</orig> my  
 money to Pap and I <orig reg="wrote">rote</orig> to him to <orig  
 reg="give">giv</orig> it to you.  I sent you sixty five <orig  
 reg="dollars">dollers</orig> and let me me <orig reg="know">now</orig> if <orig  
 reg="gave it">givit</orig> to you <orig reg="or">er</orig> not.  I <orig  
 reg="wrote">rote</orig> you a letter <orig reg="several">severl</orig> days Ago  
 and I <orig reg="put">poot</orig> <orig reg="one">won</orig> <orig  
 reg="dollar">doller</orig> and ten <orig reg="cents">sense</orig> in it and I am  
 going to<pb n="4"/> <orig reg="put">poot</orig> <orig reg="two">too</orig> <orig  
 reg="dollars">dollers</orig> in this letter.  So nothing more at present but  
 remain your husband.</p> 
  
 <closer> 
